SIMPLE: underhung
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underhung
<hw>Un`der*hung"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>Resting on a track at the bottom, instead of
being suspended; -- said of a sliding door.</def>
<rj><au>Forney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the lower jaw projecting.</def> <rj><au>T.
Hughes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underjaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Underhung
<hw>Un"der*hung"</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of an automobile body,
suspended from the springs in such a manner that the frame of the
chassis is below the axles, the object being to lower the center of
gravity of the car.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undersoil</ent>⟦br⟧
